PN,43701
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1773056483
OL,3,CDad-of-three electrocuted to death
OL,4,Cafter safety warnings were ignored
OL,6,FThe death of a man electrocuted when a
OL,7,Fcherry picker hit an 11,000-volt
OL,8,Foverhead power line was "entirely
OL,9,Fpreventable," an expert from the
OL,10,FHealth and Safety Executive (HSE) has
OL,11,Fsaid.
OL,13,FCarl Parsons, 34, was killed when the
OL,14,Fvehicle hit the power lines at the
OL,15,FWilland Biogas site in Cullompton on
OL,16,FJune 1, 2020. The incident left his
OL,17,Fcolleague, Luke Madavan, with life-
OL,18,Fchanging injuries, as the electrical
OL,19,Fcurrent passed through the mechanics
OL,20,Fof the vehicle.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1773056483
OL,3,CDad-of-three electrocuted to death
OL,4,Cafter safety warnings were ignored
OL,6,FThe court heard that New Wave Marine
OL,7,Fwas contacted by Willand O&M to lift
OL,8,Fthe lid off a biodigester and stir a
OL,9,Fcrust blockage that had formed inside
OL,10,Fthe tank.
OL,12,FDuring this work, a cherry picker
OL,13,Foperated by New Wave Marine struck and
OL,14,Foverhead power line. The electrical
OL,15,Fcurrent passed through the metal
OL,16,Fbasket, fatally electrocuting Carl and
OL,17,Fcausing a serious electric shock to
OL,18,FLuke.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1773056483
OL,3,CDad-of-three electrocuted to death
OL,4,Cafter safety warnings were ignored
OL,6,FCarl, who lived in Plymouth, was
OL,7,Fremembered by his family as funny,
OL,8,Floving, kind and a fantastic father,
OL,9,Fwho was well-loved by everyone who
OL,10,Fknew him. He left behind a wife and
OL,11,Fthree children.
OL,13,FAn investigation by the Health and
OL,14,FSafety Executive (HSE) found the
OL,15,FWilland O&M had been advised to
OL,16,Frelocate the overhead powerline by
OL,17,FWestern Power Distribution. This would
OL,18,Fhave eliminated the risk of contact
OL,19,Fduring the 2020 incident.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1773056483
OL,3,CDad-of-three electrocuted to death
OL,4,Cafter safety warnings were ignored
OL,6,FWilland O&M did not act on this and
OL,7,Fput no adequate control measures in
OL,8,Fplace, including height restrictors on
OL,9,Fcherry pickers or work areas. The HSE
OL,10,Finvestigation also found supervision,
OL,11,Fmonitoring and site induction to be
OL,12,Fpoor.
OL,14,FNew Wave Marine's risk assessment was
OL,15,Falso found to be neither suitable or
OL,16,Fsufficient. The company lacked formal
OL,17,Ftraining provision and adequate
OL,18,Fsupervision for the work carried out,
OL,19,Fthe HSE stated.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1773056483
OL,3,CDad-of-three electrocuted to death
OL,4,Cafter safety warnings were ignored
OL,6,FWilland O&M Ltd of Cleave Farm,
OL,7,FStation Road, Willand, Cullompton,
OL,8,FDevon, pleaded guilty to an offence
OL,9,Funder Regulation 3(1)(a) of the
OL,10,FElectricity at Work Regulations 1989
OL,11,Fby virtue of Regulation 14, having
OL,12,Ffailed to ensure that persons carrying
OL,13,Fout work at the site were not working
OL,14,Fon or near a live conductor without
OL,15,Freasonable and suitable precautions in
OL,16,Fplace to prevent injury.
OL,18,FThe company was fined #51,000 and
OL,19,Fordered to pay prosecution costs of
OL,20,F#28,467.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1773056483
OL,3,CDad-of-three electrocuted to death
OL,4,Cafter safety warnings were ignored
OL,6,FNew Wave Marine Ltd pleaded guilty to
OL,7,Foffences under Regulation 3(1) of the
OL,8,FManagement of Health and Safety at
OL,9,FWork Regulations 1999 and Regulation
OL,10,F4(1) of the Work at Height Regulations
OL,11,F2005.
OL,13,FThe company was fined #30,000 with
OL,14,Fprosecution costs of #8,000.
OL,16,FHSE Inspector Nicole Buchanan said:
OL,17,F"Working underneath overhead power
OL,18,Flines is inherently unsafe and these
OL,19,Frisks should be eliminated wherever
OL,20,Fpossible.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1773056483
OL,3,CDad-of-three electrocuted to death
OL,4,Cafter safety warnings were ignored
OL,6,F"There is a risk that workers
OL,7,Foperating equipment could either make
OL,8,Fdirect contact with the electrical
OL,9,Fsource or be exposed to electricity
OL,10,Farcing over several metres and
OL,11,Ftravelling through the basket.
OL,13,F"The electricity network will provide
OL,14,Fguidance and assist in moving lines or
OL,15,Fburying them underground to prevent
OL,16,Fincidents. Companies should always
OL,17,Fseek competent health and safety
OL,18,Fadvice and ensure their staff are
OL,19,Fadequately trained.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1773056483
OL,3,CDad-of-three electrocuted to death
OL,4,Cafter safety warnings were ignored
OL,6,F"The death of Mr Carl Parsons and the
OL,7,Finjuries to Mr Madavan were entirely
OL,8,Favoidable and I hope that this case
OL,9,Fwill serve as a lesson to others who
OL,10,Ftry to avoid costs by working near
OL,11,Foverhead power lines.
OL,13,F"I express my deepest sympathy to
OL,14,Fthose who witnessed the incident, to
OL,15,FCarl's family, his wife, and
OL,16,Fespecially to his three children, and
OL,17,Fto Mr Madavan; and I thank them for
OL,18,Ftheir cooperation throughout the
OL,19,Finvestigation."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
